title: State-Sponsored Terrorism, Crimes, Lies - Collection 29 (Egypt)
description:
State-Sponsored Terrorism, Crimes, and Lies - Collection 29 (Egypt):

We have 41 titles in this collection. The emphasis is on the atrocities committed by the current military regime in Egypt led by Abdul-Fattah Al-Sisi that overthrew Mohammad Morsi, the first democratically-elected president. It is unfortunate that the U.S. and other Western democracies are repeating the same mistakes in the Middle East by supporting Al-Sisi and his oppressive fascist regime in an outrageous disregard to democratic values. This creates a fertile ground for the growth of extremism and terrorism.

Many of the titles here are official reports or published articles
